    <div class="post quote">
      
      <span class="permalink">
          <a href="../post/19958463198/in-a-way-the-power-of-dissent-is-the-power-of">Mar 26, 2012</a><br />
          
      </span>
      
      <div class="realpost"><div>
        <blockquote class="thequote">In a way, the power of dissent is the power of surprise. After hearing someone shout out an errant answer, we work to understand it, which causes us to reassess our initial assumptions and try out new perspectives. “Authentic dissent can be difficult, but it’s always invigorating,” Nemeth says. “It wakes us right up.</blockquote>
        &mdash;<a href="http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2012/01/30/120130fa_fact_lehrer?currentPage=all">Brainstorming Doesn’t Really Work&#160;: The New Yorker</a>
